*** About ***
The scripts in this folder (using MATLAB 2014b & GDAL framework package 1.11) reproduce the analysis, validation, and investigation of supraglacial lake depths in Greenland with Landsat 8 (and some other multispectral sensors). How all of the scripts work together is documented in the workflow information (see below). Note that some MATLAB scripts (developed in 2014b) require the MATLAB Mapping Toolbox (Version 4.0.2) and the Optimization Toolbox (Version 7.1). In addition, some manual steps (see Workflow diagram) are carried out using QGIS (www.qgis.org)

*** Workflow Information ***
___________________Pope_SupraglacialLake_Workflow.png: Full workflow details

*** Folder Structure ***
The subfolders in this repository mirror the modular pieces of the workflow involved in the research process, namely:
*InSitu: Using In Situ spectra and depth measurements from a supraglacial lake in Greenland to test the theoretical performance of a range of satellite based multispectral lake depth retrievals
*Depth: Taking Landsat 8 data and calculating lake depths, specifically for the case study are of this work (Sermeq Kujalleq / Jakobshavn area, Greenland)
*WorldView: Processing information for WorldView Stereo digital elevation models
*Validation: Comparing WorldView DEMs and lake depth retrievals to identify the best performance
*LakeAnalysis: Using the Band 4 & Band 8 average (identified as best in Validation) to investigate the behaviour of lake depths in the Jakobshavn region in summer 2014

